What you need to know:  Athletes will only qualify for global events by competing at the national trials, national championships and Kip Keino Classic Continental Tour or any other international race recognised by World AthleticsAccording to Athletics Kenya, these measures will ensure that only the right athletes will represent the country since Kenya is in Category A of doping offendersThe qualifying window for the global event started in July last year and will end in July 31 for most of the events